Self-propulsion can be modeled by means of a force vector, applied on the center of mass of each microswimmer with dynamics independent on the particle position1,3. In particular, we consider a two-dimensional system of N interacting active particles, whose dynamics is described by over-damped Langevin equations for the positions, xi, of each particle:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
